{"first_name":"Neil","last_name":"Rimer","permalink":"neil-rimer","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/neil-rimer","homepage_url":null,"birthplace":null,"twitter_username":null,"blog_url":null,"blog_feed_url":null,"affiliation_name":"Last.fm","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":null,"alias_list":null,"created_at":"Wed Oct 17 11:07:29 UTC 2007","updated_at":"Sun Apr 25 15:58:30 UTC 2010","overview":"<p>Neil Rimer is a co-founder and Partner of Index Ventures. In 1992, Neil started the venture capital activity of Index&#8217;s predecessor firm, later co-founding Index Ventures and raising the firm&#8217;s first fund in 1996.</p>\n\n<p>Neil&#8217;s current investment focus is on innovative solutions for energy and environmental problems.</p>\n\n<p>He is currently on the board of Weatherbill, AlertMe, Lehigh Technologies, Netvibes, Moo Print, Photobox, Innovative Silicon, Pulsic, AdMarvel and DoubleTwist. Neil sponsored many of the firm&#8217;s investments including Betfair, Ofoto (now Kodak), Trolltech (now Nokia) Listen (now Real Networks), Numerical Technologies (now Synopsis) and Genmab (SDE: GNA). He has also served on the Board of Directors of U.C. Sampdoria, a football club competing in the Italian Serie A.</p>\n\n<p>Before starting Index Ventures, Neil spent four years with Montgomery Securities in San Francisco. Neil has a BA. in History and Economics from Stanford University and a MBA from Harvard Business School.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,150],"assets/images/resized/0008/4863/84863v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[200,200],"assets/images/resized/0008/4863/84863v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[200,200],"assets/images/resized/0008/4863/84863v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":""},"degrees":[],"relationships":[{"is_past":false,"title":"Co-Founder and Partner ","firm":{"name":"Index Ventures","permalink":"index-ventures","type_of_entity":"financial_org","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,68],"assets/images/resized/0005/1550/51550v1-